original: Baude, Elsa Matilda, skådespelerska, Göteborg, f. i Sthlm av Carl Pal-mén o. Johanna Svensson. G. 1. 04 m. regissör Thor Christiernsson; 2. 20 m. skådesp. Sture Baude, d. 46. Barn: Hans Sturesson, Eva Louise, Gurli Elsa Ingegärd. — Började v. Emil Hillbergs sällsk. 01, eng. v. Folkteat. i Sthlm 02-03, h. Emil von der Osten 03-04, h. Hjalmar Selander 04-06, v. Folkteat. i Gbg 06-09, v. Dramat, teat. 09-11, v. Intima teat. 11-15, h. Ranft 15-23, h. Ernst Eklund 24-29, v. Blancheteat. 30-33, v. Stadsteat. i Gbg sed. 36. Bl. roller: titelrollen i Ester, Louise i Oväder, Frun i Jul, Vivan i Aftonstjärnan, Modern i Alla ha rätt. Modern i Mäster Olof.
translated: Baude, Elsa Matilda, actress, Gothenburg, born in Stockholm to Carl Palmén and Johanna Svensson. Married 1st in 1904 to director Thor Christiernsson; 2nd in 1920 to actor Sture Baude, who died in 1946. Children: Hans Sturesson, Eva Louise, Gurli Elsa Ingegärd. Started with Emil Hillberg's company in 1901, followed by engagements at the Folk Theatre in Stockholm in 1902-1903, with Emil von der Osten in 1903-1904, with Hjalmar Selander in 1904-1906, with the Folk Theatre in Gothenburg in 1906-1909, with the Drama Theatre in 1909-1911, with the Intimate Theatre in 1911-1915, with Gustaf Ranft in 1915-1923, with Ernst Eklund in 1924-1929, with the Blanche Theatre in 1930-1933, and with the City Theatre in Gothenburg since 1936. Notable roles: the title role in Ester, Louise in Oväder, Mrs. in Jul, Vivan in Aftonstjärnan, and the mother in Alla ha rätt and Mäster Olof.
